  "notes": "Iñupiaq (Iñupiatun), Inuit language of northern Alaska. Latin orthography (Webster–Zibell, 1970s); the values above follow the North Slope dialect. Three vowel qualities /a i u/, each with a long counterpart written double (aa, ii, uu) and therefore derivable from the single-vowel mapping. ⟨g⟩ = /ɣ/ vs ⟨ġ⟩ = /ʁ/; ⟨ł⟩ = voiceless lateral /ɬ/; ⟨sr⟩ = /ʂ/. Seward Peninsula and Uummarmiutun dialects differ slightly and are not separately modelled.",
